  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>Some bite-size are easy depending on the knowledge set of the person, true. Maybe 
adding more tags on why it's bite-size? So, for example, I could look for bite-size 
css bugs but could ignore bite-size server bugs (that someone else would love to 
do).

As to what "bite-size" means, on the Volunteer Opportunities page, it does say 
"Toughness" and "What's this" for the definition. The location of the definition 
window is a little odd though. 

There are just "bite-size" bugs, right? So maybe that column could be dropped? And 
an intro text saying that these are the more simple bugs to help get people involved 
in the projects, etc.

Maybe we could make "Recommended bugs" be tailored? It says that it's based on 
profile. Should we say that that is one of the benefits of signing up to OpenHatch? 
Allow a preview? We do mention this on the front and link to volunteer finder but 
that we can even be recommend bugs is neat.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
